    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter closing Neovim and reopening, moving to the next/previous mark with \n\n    [' ]' [` ]`\n\nresults in an error. The marks can still be moved towards directly with `m`, and after doing so that specific mark now properly be used for [' etc. Tested with [a-zA-Z] marks.\nError message:\n`E92: Buffer 0 not found`\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUsing any file with text, to be able to place the marks and see the motions:\n\nnvim file.txt\njjma\n:q\nnvim file.txt\n]' -- Error\n'a -- Motion works correctly\nk]' -- Motion now works correctly\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n]' motions should function for all available marks.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, this works correctly in vim 9.2.428\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11 Pro, Version 10.0.26200 Build 26200\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nTested on Windows Terminal v1.23.20211.0 and Wezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nNot set\n\n### Installation\n\nTested stable with Winget and latest nightly from Github releases",
